title: Grateful Dead Live at Metropolitan Sports Center on 1989-04-17
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Iko Iko, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Far From Me, Built To Last, Victim Or The Crime, Bertha

Set 2

Cold Rain & Snow, Samson & Delilah, Crazy Fingers, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Jam*-> The Wheel-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> Wharf Rat-> Not Fade Away, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

*Jerry played a *new* guitar

reviews.review_text: Last dance Nice Charlie Miller soundboard of the Dead's last visit to the North Star state. Saw them in 77(perhaps the best) and 86(perhaps the worst), and wish I'd seen a few more. Official releases from Minnesota include Dicks Pick's 26 from the Labor Temple in 69, St. Paul 77, St. Paul 78. Appreciate the ability to go back and hear these great sounding shows. Thanks.
